Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the onion and @sugar{1%tsp} for the onions to the pan and stir-fry until
softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain naans{2} onto a #baking tray{}.

Divide the @marinara sauce{120%g} between the naans and spread with the back
of a #spoon{}, leaving a 1cm border.

Top with the onions, then sprinkle over the grated Cheddar.

When the oven is hot, bake your naanizzas on the top shelf until the cheese is
golden and bubbling, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Once the naanizzas are ready, crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} on
top.

Drizzle over the @fresh pesto{32%g}.

Share the naanizzas between your plates.

Add a handful of @wild rocket{40%g} alongside and drizzle the
@balsamic glaze{12%g} over the leaves to finish.

Enjoy!